issue.title: Add iOS/macOS static framework

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: Add iOS/macOS static framework

**Motivation and Context**
- A recent issue #8237, the reason of the dynamic framework rejection is still under investigation, it is necessary to create a static framework to unblock.
- Use building param `--build_apple_framework` will build both dynamic and static framework
- Now the framework becomes c++ only, c API can still be used but has to be compiled using c++
- Modified E2E test to test both static and dynamic framework, removed c API test
- Modified the pods assemble script
- Corrected some comments from a previous commit

body: @HideOnBushTuT, we recently made a new change #8357 which makes it possible to generate the static framework for onnxruntime, and hopefully this would unblock you, please give it a try.

@HideOnBushTuT please try the newly published onnxruntime-mobile-c 1.8.2 on CocoaPods, which should resolve this issue.
If some of the operators in your model is not included in our [pre-built package](https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/reference/mobile/prebuilt-package/1.8%20ORTMobilePackageOperatorTypeSupport), you would need to perform a [custom build](https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/how-to/mobile/custom-build.html)
